FBIS4-42054 "drsov126_s_94002" FBIS-SOV-94-126 Daily Report 29 Jun 1994 Georgia Patsatsia Denies Refugees Arriving in Gali Region Patsatsia Denies Refugees Arriving in Gali Region LD2906202594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1758 GMT 29 Jun 94 LD2906202594 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] The Georgian Prime-Minister Otar Patsatsia has categorically denied Abkhaz reports about the beginning of the mass uncontrolled arrival of Georgian refugees in the Gali region. At a meeting with the local administration and law enforcement officers in Zugdidi on Wednesday he said false reports are spread to undermine the normal return of refugees. The prime-minister said that the most important stage after the appearance of peace-keeping forces in the security zone is the return of refugees. Any obstacles to the process should be removed. Everything is going to be done in keeping with the four-sided agreements.
